Modifications
-------------
  Modified by: Storm Atronach
  Year:        2026

Summary of changes:

  * Threading model rework. The original CullingThreadpool used std::thread
    plus an mKillThreads atomic flag for worker shutdown. This was replaced
    with C++20 std::jthread and stop_token-driven cooperative cancellation.
    Worker shutdown now propagates via stop_callback rather than a polled
    flag, simplifying lifecycle management at suspend / kill / clear-buffer
    boundaries. Affected files:

      - CullingThreadpool.cpp
      - CullingThreadpool.h
      - MaskedOcclusionCulling.cpp
      - MaskedOcclusionCulling.h
      - MaskedOcclusionCullingAVX2.cpp
      - MaskedOcclusionCullingAVX512.cpp
      - MaskedOcclusionCullingCommon.inl
      - CompilerSpecific.inl

    The change is functional-equivalent in steady-state behavior; the
    visible difference is shutdown semantics (no polling latency) and
    slightly simplified call-site code. No public API changes.

The original Apache 2.0 copyright headers in each source file are
preserved unchanged. A short "Modified by" notice has been added below
the original header in each file we changed, per Apache 2.0 §4(b).
